	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1" facs="R 87-11 17 (04)"/>
			<p>The text of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-335" type="subject">anti-Jewish law</term> ‚<term
					ref="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Law_for_Protection_of_the_Nation">Law on the Defense of the Nation</term>‘ passed in its
				entirety on <date when="1940-12-26">December 26</date> has not been published. With only 49000 <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">Jews</term> here of a good class and holding no
				important <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-948" type="subject">government</term> positions there was no
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-351" type="subject">Jewish problem</term>. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-950" type="subject">law</term> is said to be drastic in its terms but a
				loophole in its strict enforcement may be the fact that rules and regulations for the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-950" type="subject">laws</term> application drawn up by the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000132">Minister of the Interior</term> must be approved by the <orgName
					ref="#ehri_dr_bulgaria_council_of_ministers">Council of Ministers</orgName>. I find the <term
					ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_bulgarians">Bulgarian</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term> as a whole apathetic about it and a
				little ashamed.</p>
		</body>
